dragonus18:

wtf’s a harp seal?

Harp seals resemble harbor seals in body and head form, but are larger: adult Harp Seals grow to 1.7 m (5.6 ft) long and can weigh over 130 kg (290 lb). The baby Harp seals are all white, which helps them blend in with the snow. Adults are grey or white with black markings on their back and on their head. Polar Bears, sharks, Orcas, and in some areas Walruses are natural predators of Harp Seals. Inuits living in the region hunt them mainly for sport and to a lesser extent, commercial reasons. They are often given different names according to their age
